.TH "TAKO" "1" "Jun 2026" "Tako CLI" "Tako CLI Manual"

.SH NAME
tako-rollback - Rollback to previous deployment


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBtako rollback [deployment-id] [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Rollback to a previous deployment.

.PP
If no deployment-id is provided, rolls back to the most recent successful deployment.
Specify a deployment-id to rollback to a specific deployment.

.PP
Rollback reads the freshest reachable deployment history from the mesh.

.PP
Use 'tako history' to view available deployments.

.PP
Examples:
  tako rollback --service web                 # Rollback to previous deployment
  tako rollback --service web deploy-123      # Rollback to specific deployment


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for rollback

.PP
\fB--service\fP=""
	Service to rollback (required)


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--config\fP=""
	config file (default is ./tako.yaml or ./tako.json)

.PP
\fB-e\fP, \fB--env\fP=""
	environment to deploy (default: production or only environment)

.PP
\fB--host-key-mode\fP=""
	SSH host key verification mode: tofu, strict, ask (default: tofu)

.PP
\fB-v\fP, \fB--verbose\fP[=false]
	verbose output


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBtako(1)\fP
